Ispaghula husk is not to be used by patients with a sudden change in bowel habit that persists for more than 2 weeks, undiagnosed rectal bleeding and failure to defaecate following the use of a laxative.
Ispaghula husk is also not to be used by patients suffering from abnormal constrictions in the gastro-intestinal tract, with diseases of the oesophagus and cardia, potential or existing intestinal blockage (ileus), paralysis of the intestine or megacolon, diabetes mellitus, which is difficult to regulate.
Patients with known hypersensitivity to Ispaghula husk should not use Ispaghula husk preparations.
